definition.value: A group derived from toluene by removal of a hydrogen atom from the ring carbon atom.
A group derived from toluene by removal of a hydrogen atom from the ring carbon atom at the 2-position.
A group derived from toluene by removal of a hydrogen atom from the ring carbon atom at the 3-position.
A group derived from toluene by removal of a hydrogen atom from the ring carbon atom at the 4-position.
A diterpenoid with a tetracyclic skeleton.
A chondroitin sulfate in which the site of sulfation is positions 4 and 6 of the N-acetylgalactosamine (GalNAc) sugar.
A 2,5-dihydro-1,3-thiazole having 2-carboxy-, 4-methyl- and 5-[(2-phosphonooxy)ethylidene]-substituents.
A 1-alkyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate in which the 1-alkyl substituent can be any alk-1-enyl group.
A glycerol-1-phosphate compound having an alk-1-enyl substituent at the 3-position.
A glycerol compound having an alk-1-enyl substituent in the 1-position
A glycotriaosylceramide having alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl as the glycotriaosyl component.
An acyl derivative of phosphatidic acid whose phosphorus acid component is esterified with 2-N-arachidonoylaminoethanol.
An inositol compound having acylglucosaminyl and phosphatidyl substituents on its hydroxy groups.
An acyl derivative of phosphatidic acid whose phosphorus acid component is esterified with 2-N-all-trans-retinylideneaminoethanol.
A glycerol ether having at least one alkyl substituent on oxygen.
A glycerophosphate compound having alkyl and acyl substituents on the glycerol hydroxy groups and its phosphorus acid component esterified with 2-aminoethanol
Tetrahydroporphyrins in which the saturated carbon atoms are located at nonfused carbon atoms of two diagonally opposite pyrrole rings.
Tetrahydroporphyrins in which the saturated carbon atoms are located at nonfused carbon atoms of two adjacent pyrrole rings.
An inositol compound having alpha-mannosyl-(1->2)-alpha-mannosyl-(1->6)-alpha-2-(2-aminoethylphosphoryl)mannosyl-beta-glucosaminyl and phosphatidyl substituents on its hydroxy groups.
An inositol compound having alpha-mannosyl-beta-glucosaminyl and phosphatidyl substituents on its hydroxy groups.
An inositol compound having alpha-mannosyl-(1->6)-alpha-2-(2-aminoethylphosphoryl)mannosyl-beta-glucosaminyl and phosphatidyl substituents on its hydroxy groups.
An inositol compound having alpha-2-(2-aminoethylphosphoryl)mannosyl-beta-glucosaminyl and phosphatidyl substituents on its hydroxy groups.
A glycerophosphate compound having an alkyl substituent at the 2-position of the glycerol moiety and its phosphorus acid component esterified with choline.
An acyl derivative of phosphatidic acid whose phosphorus acid component is esterified with an N-(2-hydroxyethyl)dihydropyridine bisretinoid
A glucuronic acid compound having a bile alcohol substituent at the anomeric position.
An acyl derivative of phosphatidic acid whose phosphorus acid component is esterified with an N-(2-hydroxyethyl)pyridinium bisretinoid
A nanometre-sized wire composed of either organic or inorganic substances.
An N-acylceramide compound having an isoglobopentaosyl substituent at its primary hydroxy group.
A 1-alkyl-2-acylglycerol that has S-configuration.
A glycotetraosylceramide compound having an isoglobotetraosyl moiety attached to the primary hydroxy group of the ceramide.
A ganglioside GA2 compound sulfated at the 3-position of the galactose ring
A ganglioside GA2 compound sulfated at the 3-positions of both the galactose and galactosamine rings
A ganglioside GA2 compound sulfated at the 3-position of the galactosamine ring.

An oligoglycosylceramide consisting of a branched nonasaccharide made up from five sialyl residues, two galactose residues, one N-acetylgalactosamine residue and a glucose residue at the reducing end attached to N-acylsphingosine via a beta-linkage.
An sn-glycerophosphoserine compound having an acyl substituent at the 1-hydroxy position.
